Hi Chuck,

I&#39;m not sure I understand your question, but the &quot;u&quot; sound in up is
represented by the 36th letter in Quickscript. This letter is the arc
described by the upper left quadrant of a circle. If you have Jerome
installed on your keyboard it is obtained by pressing lower case a.

The sound is called a schwa and is frequently represented by an upside down
e as in the International Phonetic Alphabet.

If you have Jerome installed on your computer and if your e-mail program can
take fonts, you can see &quot;u&quot; sound below:

a

